{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require schools to allow students to wear skirts",
        "additional_details": "We think uniforms shouldn\u2019t be used to enforce conformity and banning skirts could limit self-expression and set a precedent for further restrictions. \r\n \r\nWe think preventing students wearing skirts could:\r\nOver-centralise control: Imposes blanket policies that ignore local community values.\r\nStifle debate: Eliminates parents\u2019 and students\u2019 voices in uniform decisions.\r\nErase individuality: Denies young people the choice to express themselves.\r\nDistract from core education: Focuses energy on appearance over learning.\r\nMislabel conformity as equality:  True inclusion offers options, not bans.",
        "background": "Some schools are removing skirts entirely from uniforms, erasing choice under the guise of equality. We think this isn\u2019t inclusion, it\u2019s control. Let\u2019s stand together and demand that this be debated now. ",
